Population in Wuhan China11.08 million
Coronavirus is named after its crown-like shape—corona being Latin for 'crown'—and has killed at least 170 people and infected thousands more.

How many people are hospitalized from the flue every year?
The Centers for Disease Control & Prevention (CDC) estimates that, on average, more than 200,000 people in United States are hospitalized every year for influenza-related heart & respiratory complications.
How many people die from the flu each year?
The CDC estimates that as many as 56,000 people die from the flue or flu-like illness each year.
How many people die from tetanus a year?
The World Health Organization (WHO) estimate about 280,000 people die of tetanus worldwide each year, mostly in developing countries…around 210,000 of these deaths are children.
